\p{This PR adds basic definitions for the flat modality. I wanted to also add
the right adjoint sharp modality but this proved more compex than it first seemed.
See [experimental/sharp](https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/tree/experimental/sharp)
for progress in that direction, as well as the [modal type theory](stt-0050) tree.}

\ul{
  \li{An introduction to [modal type theory](stt-0050)}
  \li{Adds \ref{Modalities.Flat.Flat}}
  \li{Show #{\modflat{-}}is an [idempotent](stt-0054) [comonadic](stt-0052) [functor](stt-0051)}
  \li{Defines crisp sigma types, and shows [[stt-0053]]}
  \li{Defines crisp identity induction, showing that lex-ness follows from this}
}
